South Africa’s net foreign reserves inched up to $43.659 billion in February from $43.589 billion in January, the Reserve Bank said on Thursday. Gross reserves also edged higher, rising to $50.836 billion from $50.832 billion previously, central bank data showed. The forward position, which represents the central bank’s unsettled or swap transactions, fell to $1.369 billion in February from $1.382 billion in the previous month.